
<item rdf:about='http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-feng-dmm-ra-prefixtype-03.txt'>
    <title>"Router Advertisement Prefix Option Extension for On-Demand Mobility", Wu-chi Feng, Danny Moses</title>
    <link>http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-feng-dmm-ra-prefixtype-03.txt</link>
    <description>Router Advertisement / Router Solicitation is one of the ways for hosts to establish network IPv6 connectivity configuration.  This document describes two approches to allowing a router to specify mobility service type availability to mobile hosts.  Mobile hosts can then configure their IP address to the preferred type of mobile connectivity.  Two possibilities are considered: (i) creating an extension to the router advertisement prefix information option to allow the router to specify mobility connectivity types, and (ii) specifying a new RA options that allows the router to specify the mobility connectivity types.</description>
    <dc:date>2018-09-12T07:00:00-00:00</dc:date>
</item>
